1
00:00:39,733 --> 00:00:41,000
<i> What's the matter?</i>

2
00:00:41,133 --> 00:00:42,567
<i> You always seem preoccupied.</i>

3
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:44,100
<i> This is about your father.</i>

4
00:00:44,233 --> 00:00:45,800
<i> He is here in the Philippines.</i>

5
00:00:45,933 --> 00:00:48,500
<i> Andrea, you need to calm down.</i>

6
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:50,467
<i>If you face them
while you're angry,</i>

7
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:51,933
<i> it will only cause trouble.</i>

8
00:00:52,067 --> 00:00:53,333
<i> One-way ticket to Manila?</i>

9
00:00:53,467 --> 00:00:54,200
<i> Seriously?</i>

10
00:00:54,333 --> 00:00:55,867
<i> I'm going to a war, Alice.</i>

11
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,433
Friend, you'll be fighting alone

12
00:00:57,567 --> 00:01:00,200
<i> I was born ready, Alice.</i>

13
00:01:00,333 --> 00:01:02,300
<i>Why are you so stubborn, Coleen?</i>

14
00:01:02,433 --> 00:01:03,767
<i>Didn't I already talk to you
about this?</i>

15
00:01:03,900 --> 00:01:06,033
<i> Andrea, give that back!</i>

16
00:01:06,167 --> 00:01:07,167
- Hello?
- Andrea!

17
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:08,533
Jessica!

18
00:01:08,700 --> 00:01:10,467
Please stop communicating
with my sister.

19
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:12,533
We don't care about your father!

20
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:13,433
Andrea!

21
00:01:13,567 --> 00:01:14,400
Stop!

22
00:01:14,533 --> 00:01:16,100
Give that back!

23
00:01:16,233 --> 00:01:18,433
We're already messed up
because of your father.

24
00:01:18,567 --> 00:01:20,133
So please, leave us alone!

25
00:01:20,267 --> 00:01:21,800
We're trying to live in peace!

26
00:01:21,933 --> 00:01:25,333
- And if you don't...
- Andrea, this is Rona.

27
00:01:27,833 --> 00:01:28,833
Rona?

28
00:01:30,367 --> 00:01:31,567
Sorry, I thought you were...

29
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:33,167
Give it back!

30
00:01:37,067 --> 00:01:38,367
Hello...

31
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:40,200
Bestie, I'm sorry about that.

32
00:01:40,333 --> 00:01:41,400
I'll call you back later.

33
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:48,067
Andrea, what are you doing?

34
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,533
Are you seriously
going to interfere

35
00:01:49,667 --> 00:01:51,133
with my phone calls as well?

36
00:01:51,267 --> 00:01:53,400
You're being too much!

37
00:01:53,533 --> 00:01:55,000
Sorry, Coleen.

38
00:01:55,133 --> 00:01:57,367
You are such an emabarrassment!

39
00:01:57,500 --> 00:01:59,133
You should at least check

40
00:01:59,267 --> 00:02:02,300
who you're picking a fight with
before you start it!

41
00:02:02,433 --> 00:02:03,733
I said, I'm sorry!

42
00:02:03,867 --> 00:02:05,467
What else do you want?

43
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:08,600
Stop meddling with my life!
That's what I want!

44
00:02:10,567 --> 00:02:11,967
You're being disrespectful!

45
00:02:12,100 --> 00:02:13,033
I'm being disrespectful?

46
00:02:13,167 --> 00:02:16,600
Who's not respecting privacy
around here?

47
00:02:16,767 --> 00:02:18,300
Me?

48
00:02:18,433 --> 00:02:19,967
Are you really calling me out?

49
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:22,267
When you told Mom
to hide the truth

50
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,200
about your father from us...

51
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:26,767
Was that not disrespectful?

52
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:29,567
So, who's being disrespectful
now?

53
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:30,900
Go ahead,

54
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:33,200
go on,
why don't you argue even louder?

55
00:02:33,333 --> 00:02:36,067
Since your mom hasn't
heard you yet anyway!

56
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,800
Do you want a microphone?

57
00:02:37,933 --> 00:02:39,233
I'll get you one!

58
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,467
We need to find
you a real therapist, Dad.

59
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:52,633
This might not be the proper way
to do this.

60
00:02:53,833 --> 00:02:56,000
I just looked it up
on the internet.

61
00:02:56,133 --> 00:02:58,133
We'll find one later, Jessica.

62
00:02:58,267 --> 00:03:00,667
It's not a priority
at the moment.

63
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:05,267
Did Felma or Coleen
message you yet?

64
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:09,067
I messaged Miss Felma, and
I gave her my Philippine number.

65
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:11,367
But...

66
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:13,067
she didn't reply.

67
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:14,600
I guess she's busy.

68
00:03:15,667 --> 00:03:17,700
Perhaps she no longer
wants to talk to us.

69
00:03:19,233 --> 00:03:20,600
I think she only did it
out of obligation

70
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:22,300
the last time we saw her.

71
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:25,267
I don't think so, Dad.

72
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,967
When we talked to them before,

73
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:29,733
they seemed okay.

74
00:03:29,867 --> 00:03:31,900
They're accommodating and kind.

75
00:03:32,033 --> 00:03:33,233
I agree, but...

76
00:03:33,367 --> 00:03:35,933
it doesn't mean that they're not
mad at me anymore.

77
00:03:36,067 --> 00:03:39,633
Perhaps they just feel bad
about what happened to me.

78
00:03:39,767 --> 00:03:42,967
Dad, let's not jump
into conclusions.

79
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:44,933
Let's just wait
for them to reply,

80
00:03:45,067 --> 00:03:48,133
and let's hope that they're
willing to meet with us.

81
00:03:48,267 --> 00:03:51,133
So you can finally ask
for Miss Felma's forgiveness

82
00:03:51,267 --> 00:03:52,700
in person.

83
00:03:52,833 --> 00:03:53,933
I hope so, Jessica.

84
00:03:55,567 --> 00:03:58,500
You know what,
that's all that I want.

85
00:03:58,633 --> 00:04:02,267
I just want to have
a clean slate.

86
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:04,133
The...

87
00:04:04,267 --> 00:04:06,833
You know, without baggage.

88
00:04:06,967 --> 00:04:09,833
You know what,
if Felma forgives me,

89
00:04:09,967 --> 00:04:15,200
it will be a blessing
for our new start in life.

90
00:04:17,733 --> 00:04:19,667
Can I borrow your phone?

91
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,900
I just want to watch
Coleen's video.

92
00:04:22,033 --> 00:04:22,967
Sure.

93
00:04:25,933 --> 00:04:27,033
Here you go.

94
00:04:32,467 --> 00:04:34,433
It's not here anymore.
I think your mom deleted it.

95
00:04:34,567 --> 00:04:36,133
No, Dad.

96
00:04:36,267 --> 00:04:37,233
Let me see.

97
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:42,467
I saved it in my SkySync.

98
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:45,733
I know how important
it is to you.

99
00:04:45,867 --> 00:04:46,833
Thank you, Jessica.

100
00:04:46,967 --> 00:04:48,500
You're welcome.

101
00:04:48,633 --> 00:04:51,667
Hello, Dad!

102
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,933
How are you?

103
00:04:54,467 --> 00:04:57,667
I'm Coleen,
your youngest daughter.

104
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:58,867
Dad...

105
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,967
You know what?

106
00:05:01,133 --> 00:05:03,533
I've been longing to do this.

107
00:05:09,967 --> 00:05:13,300
Madam, good morning.

108
00:05:13,433 --> 00:05:16,200
Madam, Value More called.

109
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:20,400
They want supplies
of longanisa, tocino,

110
00:05:20,533 --> 00:05:24,367
and sisig at all their branches.

111
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:29,267
And this one, Ma'am,
the report that you need.

112
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:31,000
Let Noah handle that one.

113
00:05:31,133 --> 00:05:33,267
He knows what to do with that.

114
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,533
He's not in the office today.

115
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:37,033
Again?

116
00:05:37,167 --> 00:05:38,900
Let Andrea handle it then.

117
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:41,233
Yes, Ma'am.

118
00:05:42,367 --> 00:05:43,300
Paz...

119
00:05:44,533 --> 00:05:47,133
Don't you dare give me
a cold shoulder.

120
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,233
Come on.

121
00:05:50,367 --> 00:05:51,700
I'm sorry.

122
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:54,467
I'm sorry about what I said.

123
00:05:57,267 --> 00:05:59,967
I'm glad you know.

124
00:06:00,100 --> 00:06:01,867
Okay, fine.

125
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,000
I forgive you.

126
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:05,867
That's it?

127
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:09,500
You're so easy to get.

128
00:06:09,667 --> 00:06:11,133
Whatever!

129
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:15,133
- Love you, Felma.
- Love you too, Paz.

130
00:06:29,033 --> 00:06:30,500
Hi, Miss Felma.

131
00:06:30,633 --> 00:06:32,167
Jessica here,

132
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:34,200
I hope I'm not a bother.

133
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:37,167
I have something
to ask you, if it's okay.

134
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:38,700
May I call?

135
00:06:53,033 --> 00:06:55,667
Oh, no! You're so stupid, Angge!

136
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,200
What am I going to do now?

137
00:06:59,333 --> 00:07:01,400
Angge, what happened?
Let me get that.

138
00:07:01,533 --> 00:07:05,233
- Ma'am. Ma'am, don't bother!
- I got it.

139
00:07:07,467 --> 00:07:09,733
Thank you, Ma'am.
Sorry about that.

140
00:07:09,867 --> 00:07:12,333
It's embarrassing.

141
00:07:12,467 --> 00:07:14,167
I'm sorry.

142
00:07:15,533 --> 00:07:17,433
- Angge.
- Yes?

143
00:07:18,533 --> 00:07:20,333
How are you...

144
00:07:20,467 --> 00:07:21,533
holding up?

145
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:25,933
It's a torture, Ma'am.

146
00:07:26,067 --> 00:07:28,533
Especially the first week
after the car accident,

147
00:07:28,667 --> 00:07:30,833
it was so hard.

148
00:07:30,967 --> 00:07:33,233
But I'm getting used to it.

149
00:07:33,367 --> 00:07:36,000
It only took me
a couple of months to adapt.

150
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:40,567
Sorry for oversharing.

151
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:42,100
I'm going back to work.

152
00:07:42,233 --> 00:07:43,500
- Okay.
- Thanks again.

153
00:07:43,633 --> 00:07:45,133
And I'm sorry again.

154
00:07:45,267 --> 00:07:46,233
Bye.

155
00:07:56,767 --> 00:07:58,200
Hello, Jessica.

156
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:03,833
Where's your dad?

157
00:08:07,733 --> 00:08:09,233
Can we meet?

158
00:08:26,933 --> 00:08:28,833
Dad, she's here.

159
00:08:52,933 --> 00:08:55,700
Yes, I arrived, Alice.

160
00:08:55,867 --> 00:08:58,433
And I'm geared up for war.

161
00:09:32,167 --> 00:09:34,500
Thank you for coming,
Miss Felma.

162
00:09:38,567 --> 00:09:40,333
So you're Jessica.

163
00:09:43,300 --> 00:09:44,967
We finally met.

164
00:09:46,233 --> 00:09:48,667
Yes, nice meeting you.

165
00:09:51,733 --> 00:09:55,433
Excuse me,
I'll be at the other table.

166
00:09:55,567 --> 00:09:57,400
- Okay.
- Excuse me.

167
00:10:26,867 --> 00:10:30,067
Felma, I know that Jessica
already said this, but...

168
00:10:32,167 --> 00:10:34,167
thank you for coming to see us.

169
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,033
I hope...

170
00:10:41,167 --> 00:10:43,800
that you'll forgive me
for everything that I've done.

171
00:10:46,833 --> 00:10:48,867
Felma, I know that it's hard.

172
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:52,600
I hope you'll understand.

173
00:10:52,733 --> 00:10:55,167
I came here to help you.

174
00:10:57,100 --> 00:10:58,533
And your daughter.

175
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,300
So you can start over.

176
00:11:02,467 --> 00:11:04,567
Because she asked me for help.

177
00:11:06,233 --> 00:11:07,833
And I'm doing it for Coleen.

178
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:11,400
Because she's worried about you.

179
00:11:12,533 --> 00:11:13,900
You should have brought her
with you.

180
00:11:14,033 --> 00:11:15,433
She doesn't know that I'm here.

181
00:11:15,567 --> 00:11:17,800
And she should never find out.

182
00:11:17,933 --> 00:11:20,967
Because I told her that...

183
00:11:21,100 --> 00:11:23,767
not to meet with you.

184
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:25,300
Felma, why?

185
00:11:25,433 --> 00:11:27,933
I don't want Andrea...

186
00:11:28,067 --> 00:11:29,933
and Jeffrey to get mad
at Coleen.

187
00:11:33,433 --> 00:11:34,167
So...

188
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:37,333
What do you and Jessica need?

189
00:11:37,467 --> 00:11:40,000
Do you need...

190
00:11:40,133 --> 00:11:41,967
money for your
everyday expenses?

191
00:11:43,700 --> 00:11:45,100
Don't be embarrassed.

192
00:11:46,967 --> 00:11:49,800
Just think that...

193
00:11:49,933 --> 00:11:52,033
I'm doing this for Coleen.

194
00:11:52,167 --> 00:11:54,400
She really wants
to help you out.

195
00:11:56,367 --> 00:11:59,067
We don't need money.

196
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:01,567
We have money to get us through.

197
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:02,500
And...

198
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:08,133
- I can get a job from...
- I will also find you a job.

199
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:11,867
Something that will fit...

200
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:14,133
your condition.

201
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:16,000
So you won't have to struggle.

202
00:12:16,967 --> 00:12:18,067
Thank you.

203
00:12:19,267 --> 00:12:20,967
What about your housing?

204
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:22,467
Do you have a place already?

205
00:12:24,667 --> 00:12:25,800
That's the thing.

206
00:12:25,933 --> 00:12:29,300
We need to find an apartment.

207
00:12:29,433 --> 00:12:31,600
And if we can get...

208
00:12:31,733 --> 00:12:33,167
a cheap one.

209
00:12:33,300 --> 00:12:35,167
The...

210
00:12:35,300 --> 00:12:38,800
The place Jessica found online
cost too much.

211
00:12:38,933 --> 00:12:39,867
Okay.

212
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:43,800
I will take care of that.

213
00:12:46,267 --> 00:12:47,433
What else do you need?

214
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:52,867
We need to find a school
for Jessica.

215
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:58,067
And if it's possible to find one
that doesn't cost too much.

216
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,300
Okay.

217
00:13:01,633 --> 00:13:08,000
You should enroll her at
Whitehills Integrated Academy.

218
00:13:08,133 --> 00:13:10,267
I know the principal
who runs the school.

219
00:13:11,633 --> 00:13:15,033
Wait, I think the tuition
is a bit costly.

220
00:13:15,167 --> 00:13:20,200
Perhaps you could try
JP Roxas Academy?

221
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:21,500
Wait,

222
00:13:21,667 --> 00:13:23,833
I'll call my client,

223
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:27,533
and I'll ask her
how much the tuition is.

224
00:13:33,133 --> 00:13:34,833
Hello, Miss Lynette?

225
00:13:34,967 --> 00:13:36,267
Hi!

226
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:39,300
Yes, this is Felma.

227
00:13:39,433 --> 00:13:41,300
I just need
to ask you something.

228
00:13:41,433 --> 00:13:46,733
I'd like to know the tuition fee
at JP Roxas Academy.

229
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:48,200
Yes.

230
00:13:48,333 --> 00:13:49,633
That will be great.

231
00:13:49,767 --> 00:13:50,733
Alright.

232
00:14:02,900 --> 00:14:05,567
Wait, this is a Canadian
phone number again.

233
00:14:09,667 --> 00:14:11,267
Hello, Bro?

234
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:13,167
Are you back in Canada already?

235
00:14:13,300 --> 00:14:15,533
This is Hazel.

236
00:14:15,667 --> 00:14:16,933
<i> Where is Manuel?</i>

237
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:20,400
<i>How would I know where he is?
Why are you asking me?</i>

238
00:14:20,533 --> 00:14:22,233
<i> Aren't you guys in Canada?</i>

239
00:14:22,367 --> 00:14:24,633
Don't try to fool me, Abel.

240
00:14:24,767 --> 00:14:27,933
I know that he has no one here
but you.

241
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,733
I don't know.

242
00:14:29,867 --> 00:14:31,233
<i> Oh really?</i>

243
00:14:31,367 --> 00:14:33,700
Do you want me to take
my anger out on you too?

244
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:40,767
If you don't tell me
where Manuel is,

245
00:14:40,900 --> 00:14:44,167
I will spill everything you did
in Saudi Arabia.

246
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:45,767
I can easily find your wife.

247
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:48,900
And I will tell her
everything that you did!

248
00:14:49,033 --> 00:14:49,500
What now?

249
00:14:49,633 --> 00:14:51,267
<i> Oh, really, Hazel?</i>

250
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:52,133
Go ahead then, tell her!

251
00:14:52,267 --> 00:14:53,967
Do you think
you could scare me?

252
00:14:57,333 --> 00:14:58,667
Hello?

253
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:07,433
Wait, wait a minute.

254
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:11,333
What is it again?
You can't call Paz!

255
00:15:11,467 --> 00:15:13,233
Wait, wait, wait.

256
00:15:13,367 --> 00:15:14,600
Here you go! Friendsbook.

257
00:15:14,733 --> 00:15:17,900
What's her password again?
Password...

258
00:15:18,033 --> 00:15:18,967
What is Paz's password?

259
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:20,600
There.

260
00:15:20,733 --> 00:15:21,967
Here you go.

261
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:23,533
Hazel...

262
00:15:25,067 --> 00:15:26,667
Cruz...

263
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:27,567
Blocked!

264
00:15:28,667 --> 00:15:31,333
There you go,
you've been blocked.

265
00:15:31,467 --> 00:15:33,067
Is it blocked already?

266
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:34,400
Okay.

267
00:15:34,533 --> 00:15:35,633
She's blocked.

268
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:39,933
Manuel, that idiot,
he'll get me in trouble.

269
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:42,867
I can't thank you enough,
Miss Felma.

270
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,567
You're a blessing to us.

271
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:46,933
You're welcome, Jessica.

272
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:49,633
We'll go ahead.

273
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:52,867
Take care.

274
00:16:46,733 --> 00:16:47,667
Paz?

275
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:49,967
You know her, Dad?

276
00:16:51,933 --> 00:16:53,033
Yes,

277
00:16:53,167 --> 00:16:56,100
she's your Uncle Abel's wife.

278
00:16:56,233 --> 00:16:57,200
Really?

279
00:17:01,733 --> 00:17:03,100
I caught you!

280
00:17:03,233 --> 00:17:04,167
Paz!

281
00:17:09,100 --> 00:17:10,833
What are you doing here?

282
00:17:10,967 --> 00:17:12,100
Who's with you?

283
00:17:12,233 --> 00:17:13,933
Don't worry,
I didn't bring anyone with me.

284
00:17:14,067 --> 00:17:16,000
I won't tell your kids
about this.

285
00:17:16,167 --> 00:17:21,633
And I will never tell
your ex-boyfriend about this.

286
00:17:21,767 --> 00:17:23,967
Felma, what the heck!

287
00:17:24,100 --> 00:17:26,233
Why did you meet with him?

288
00:17:26,367 --> 00:17:28,667
I thought you had no plans
of seeing him?

289
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:30,867
I just want to help him.

290
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,500
That's all I want to do.

291
00:17:32,633 --> 00:17:34,267
Really? I don't believe you.

292
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:36,233
It's true.

293
00:17:36,367 --> 00:17:38,500
Jessica called me.

294
00:17:38,633 --> 00:17:40,133
You know me well, don't you?

295
00:17:41,467 --> 00:17:43,333
You know I will help out
as far as I can.

296
00:17:44,767 --> 00:17:46,500
Why didn't you tell me?

297
00:17:46,633 --> 00:17:48,600
I should have come with you.

298
00:17:48,767 --> 00:17:50,133
Would you have let me
see him if you knew?

299
00:17:50,267 --> 00:17:51,433
You wouldn't have let me, right?

300
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:55,100
You have a point.

301
00:17:55,233 --> 00:17:57,867
Paz, you have to keep this
between us, okay?

302
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:59,333
Do I have a choice?

303
00:18:00,633 --> 00:18:03,633
I don't want you and your kids
to end up fighting.

304
00:18:03,767 --> 00:18:07,533
Just make sure that you won't do
anything but help them out.

305
00:18:07,667 --> 00:18:09,467
That's it, nothing else!
Noodles sounds good.

306
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:12,633
Waiter, can I have some noodles!

307
00:18:12,767 --> 00:18:13,833
Noodles, please.

308
00:18:19,633 --> 00:18:22,267
Miss Felma is so kind, Dad.

309
00:18:22,433 --> 00:18:24,800
I wish Mom were as kind as her.

310
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:28,567
Dad.

311
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:30,000
What's wrong?

312
00:18:31,267 --> 00:18:33,200
Felma has changed a lot.

313
00:18:36,033 --> 00:18:37,000
Dad...

314
00:18:37,133 --> 00:18:38,367
it's been years.

315
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:41,200
You don't expect
to see the same woman.

316
00:18:41,333 --> 00:18:43,233
Besides...

317
00:18:43,367 --> 00:18:44,367
You know...

318
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:46,067
you had a history.

319
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:48,433
I know that.

320
00:18:49,567 --> 00:18:55,833
Perhaps I just miss Felma,
who speaks gently.

321
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:59,367
I forgot that I wronged her.

322
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:00,867
But you know what,

323
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:03,733
I'm glad to see her like that.

324
00:19:03,867 --> 00:19:07,500
She has a lot of confidence now,

325
00:19:07,633 --> 00:19:10,967
like she's not afraid
to get hurt.

326
00:19:11,100 --> 00:19:13,100
What do you call that?

327
00:19:13,233 --> 00:19:15,800
Empowered? Is that it?

328
00:19:15,933 --> 00:19:17,300
Has she forgiven you?

329
00:19:18,467 --> 00:19:21,100
We haven't talked about that,
maybe...

330
00:19:21,233 --> 00:19:23,267
she doesn't want to talk
about our past.

331
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:28,133
It's still a good start, Dad.

332
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:31,767
The fact that she agreed
to see you is big!

333
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:33,900
And she's willing to help us.

334
00:19:34,033 --> 00:19:38,300
I think she just feels bad
for me.

335
00:19:38,433 --> 00:19:41,100
I didn't want
to think like that,

336
00:19:41,233 --> 00:19:44,100
but I feel like a beggar.

337
00:19:44,233 --> 00:19:46,000
Dad, don't overthink.

338
00:19:46,133 --> 00:19:47,133
Maybe you're right.

339
00:19:47,267 --> 00:19:50,833
Miss Felma pities you,
but I think there's more to it.

340
00:19:50,967 --> 00:19:52,533
I think she cares, Dad.

341
00:19:52,667 --> 00:19:55,800
Because if she doesn't,
she would have just ignored us.

342
00:19:55,933 --> 00:19:57,100
Right?

343
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:05,767
Thank you so much, Jessica.

344
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:07,700
And I'm sorry.

345
00:20:07,833 --> 00:20:10,133
You see, I'm your dad, but...

346
00:20:10,267 --> 00:20:11,333
you were the one guiding me,

347
00:20:11,467 --> 00:20:14,333
and you're taking care
of everything.

348
00:20:14,467 --> 00:20:18,000
Dad, didn't I promise
that I would take care of you?

349
00:20:19,233 --> 00:20:21,000
I will make it up to you.

350
00:20:22,233 --> 00:20:23,967
I promise you,
I will regain my strength.

351
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:26,167
That's the spirit, Dad.

352
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:30,133
But don't do it just for me,
do it for yourself too.

353
00:20:30,267 --> 00:20:31,100
Yes.

354
00:20:31,233 --> 00:20:33,067
- Promise?
- I promise.

355
00:20:40,933 --> 00:20:44,700
Promise me this is the last time
you will meet with Manuel.

356
00:20:44,833 --> 00:20:47,700
If you want to help him,
let me handle it.

357
00:20:47,833 --> 00:20:50,400
I will talk to him, okay?

358
00:20:52,133 --> 00:20:54,000
Paz.

359
00:20:54,133 --> 00:20:55,400
You can't do this to me!

360
00:20:55,533 --> 00:20:56,467
Make her come out here then!

361
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:58,033
If you don't want me
to go inside! Call her!

362
00:20:58,167 --> 00:21:00,000
I don't need an appointment!

363
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:03,333
Tell your home wrecker boss,
that flirty Felma,

364
00:21:03,467 --> 00:21:05,667
that Hazel Capistrano Cruz
is here to see her!

365
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:07,533
- Hurry up! Tell her I'm here!
- Ma'am, you can't go inside.

366
00:21:07,667 --> 00:21:10,167
What do you mean
I can't go inside?

367
00:21:10,333 --> 00:21:13,333
Oh no, Felma,
that witch is here!

368
00:21:13,967 --> 00:21:16,067
Tell your home wrecker boss,
that flirty Felma,

369
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:19,167
that Hazel Capistrano Cruz
is here to see her!

370
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:21,133
- Hurry up! Tell her I'm here!
- Ma'am, you can't go inside.

371
00:21:21,267 --> 00:21:22,900
What do you mean
I can't go inside?

372
00:21:24,100 --> 00:21:26,433
Oh no, Felma,
that witch is here!

373
00:21:26,567 --> 00:21:28,267
How did she find you here?

374
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:30,233
Our address is listed
on our website.

375
00:21:30,367 --> 00:21:31,267
Oh, that's right.

376
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:32,800
Hey, Felma!

377
00:21:32,933 --> 00:21:34,400
Get out of there!

378
00:21:34,533 --> 00:21:35,800
Do you think I didn't know
you're in there!

379
00:21:35,933 --> 00:21:39,333
Oh my gosh! Oh, no!
This is what I'm talking about.

380
00:21:39,467 --> 00:21:40,667
Whenever Manuel is around,

381
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:43,900
he brings nothing but trouble.

382
00:21:44,067 --> 00:21:46,333
Hey, hey, wait,
where are you going?

383
00:21:46,467 --> 00:21:48,900
I will avenge Coleen
for what Hazel did to her.

384
00:21:49,033 --> 00:21:51,133
That woman is really asking
for trouble.

385
00:21:51,267 --> 00:21:52,333
Felma, Felma, Felma!

386
00:21:52,467 --> 00:21:55,133
Don't do that here!
Not here, not now.

387
00:21:55,267 --> 00:21:57,067
It will be embarrassing
if your employees see that.

388
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:59,567
Just chill here, relax, okay?

389
00:21:59,700 --> 00:22:01,133
I'll take care of her.

390
00:22:01,267 --> 00:22:03,467
Stay here, don't go anywhere.

391
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:04,567
Stay put!

392
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,467
You're trying to hide her!

393
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:12,500
Let me go inside if you don't
want to call her out here!

394
00:22:12,633 --> 00:22:13,400
Hey, Felma!

395
00:22:13,533 --> 00:22:15,600
Call her! Call your boss!
Call her!

396
00:22:15,767 --> 00:22:17,467
Call your home wrecker boss!

397
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:19,733
Stop making a scene here!

398
00:22:19,867 --> 00:22:21,500
- Who are you?
- The people are looking at you!

399
00:22:21,633 --> 00:22:22,933
- Come here!
- Who are you?

400
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:28,567
- Come here!
- Let go of me!

401
00:22:28,700 --> 00:22:30,600
We'll settle this between us!
Come here!

402
00:22:30,733 --> 00:22:31,567
- Come with me!
- Why are you doing this?

403
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:32,667
You want to fight?

404
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:34,933
Fine, we'll fight!

405
00:22:35,067 --> 00:22:36,167
- Come here!
- What are you doing?

406
00:22:36,300 --> 00:22:38,633
Let's settle this!

407
00:22:39,167 --> 00:22:40,167
You witch!

408
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:44,200
If you touch me again,
I will gouge your eyes out!

409
00:22:44,333 --> 00:22:44,933
Oh, please.

410
00:22:45,067 --> 00:22:48,133
Can you shut up for a second?

411
00:22:48,300 --> 00:22:51,500
I'm not your enemy,
I'm your ally.

412
00:22:51,633 --> 00:22:53,533
What?

413
00:22:53,667 --> 00:22:55,667
Are you deaf? Can't you hear me?

414
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:57,433
I'm your ally.

415
00:22:57,567 --> 00:22:58,733
Is that clear?

416
00:22:58,867 --> 00:23:01,233
And you know what, if
you come here and make a scene,

417
00:23:01,367 --> 00:23:04,033
you'll only waste your energy.

418
00:23:04,167 --> 00:23:06,900
Excuse me, who are you?

419
00:23:07,033 --> 00:23:09,700
And why are you talking to me?
Why are you butting in?

420
00:23:09,833 --> 00:23:11,567
I'm Abel's wife.

421
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:17,300
You?

422
00:23:17,433 --> 00:23:19,267
You? You're Abel's wife?

423
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:20,967
Yes, I'm Abel's wife.

424
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:23,267
- You're the loudmouth wife?
- Yes, that's me!

425
00:23:23,433 --> 00:23:24,500
Exactly!

426
00:23:24,633 --> 00:23:29,133
So you know what's good for you
is to shut up right now

427
00:23:29,267 --> 00:23:32,467
because your mouth
is nothing compared to mine.

428
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:34,200
You might have an assault
rifle for a mouth,

429
00:23:34,333 --> 00:23:35,467
but I have a bazooka.

430
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:38,333
So just listen to me, please!

431
00:23:39,433 --> 00:23:42,133
You need my help.

432
00:23:44,533 --> 00:23:46,567
Are you on drugs?

433
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:49,633
What made you think
that I need your help?

434
00:23:51,667 --> 00:23:54,133
What if I tell you...

435
00:23:54,267 --> 00:23:56,633
that I know where Manuel is?

436
00:23:59,667 --> 00:24:01,133
<i> Bestie!</i>

437
00:24:01,267 --> 00:24:04,100
<i>Are you getting along
with Andrea now?</i>

438
00:24:04,233 --> 00:24:05,300
<i> What do you want?</i>

439
00:24:05,433 --> 00:24:08,067
<i>Stop meddling with my life,
that's what I want!</i>

440
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:09,333
<i> When you told Mom</i>

441
00:24:09,467 --> 00:24:12,167
<i>to hide the truth
about your father from us?</i>

442
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:15,633
<i>So, who is being
disrespectful now?</i>

443
00:24:15,767 --> 00:24:16,833
Not yet.

444
00:24:18,033 --> 00:24:20,067
<i>I hope you guys
can patch things up.</i>

445
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:23,000
<i>Andrea is a bit scary
when she is mad.</i>

446
00:24:23,133 --> 00:24:26,833
<i>I was shocked when she went full
blast on me on the phone.</i>

447
00:24:26,967 --> 00:24:28,100
<i> So Coleen,</i>

448
00:24:28,233 --> 00:24:31,400
<i>please don't try to contact
your half sister, okay?</i>

449
00:24:31,567 --> 00:24:34,633
<i>It might cause trouble
between you and Andrea.</i>

450
00:24:34,767 --> 00:24:38,633
I won't contact them anymore,
I will just listen to my mom.

451
00:24:38,767 --> 00:24:42,200
<i>That's right.
Just stay out of trouble.</i>

452
00:24:42,333 --> 00:24:44,333
Anyway, don't I owe you money

453
00:24:44,467 --> 00:24:46,233
for the chapter seven
you printed for me?

454
00:24:46,367 --> 00:24:47,833
How much is it?

455
00:24:47,967 --> 00:24:49,733
Ninety six pesos.

456
00:24:49,867 --> 00:24:51,600
Wait, I'll just use
the restroom real quick.

457
00:24:51,733 --> 00:24:53,900
Okay, Rona, take care. Bye.

458
00:25:34,100 --> 00:25:36,467
See? You got all speechless.

459
00:25:36,633 --> 00:25:38,900
Where's your English now?

460
00:25:41,533 --> 00:25:43,700
Why would you help me?

461
00:25:43,833 --> 00:25:48,300
Naturally, so your husband
would finally leave Felma alone.

462
00:25:48,433 --> 00:25:50,067
To get them away
from each other. Right?

463
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:52,433
Are you going to listen to me
or not?

464
00:25:55,500 --> 00:25:57,333
Okay, go ahead,

465
00:25:57,467 --> 00:25:58,833
I'm listening.

466
00:25:58,967 --> 00:26:01,400
Good, here's the plan.

467
00:26:01,533 --> 00:26:03,900
I will find out where Manuel is.

468
00:26:04,033 --> 00:26:06,800
And then I will inform you.

469
00:26:06,933 --> 00:26:09,333
And then you can go ahead
and take him

470
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:12,400
with you to Canada
for goodness sake!

471
00:26:14,933 --> 00:26:16,533
It's a win-win situation, right?

472
00:26:20,067 --> 00:26:22,267
You don't know
where Coleen went?

473
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:23,800
I don't know where she is.

474
00:26:23,933 --> 00:26:25,533
I know where Manuel is.

475
00:26:25,667 --> 00:26:28,000
They're staying at some Airbnb.

476
00:26:28,133 --> 00:26:29,367
I can finally meet you.

477
00:26:29,500 --> 00:26:31,167
I can finally see you.

478
00:26:31,300 --> 00:26:32,067
Fourth floor?

479
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,133
406.

480
00:26:33,267 --> 00:26:34,100
What's your name, Ma'am?

481
00:26:34,233 --> 00:26:35,133
Hazel.

482
00:26:43,133 --> 00:26:44,400
Dad.

483
00:26:44,533 --> 00:26:45,933
Coleen.
